-- Chilean Stock Movers: Cervecerias Unidas, Cencosud Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-05-03T21:29:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/chilean-stock-movers-cervecerias-unidas-cencosud-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  retreated 0.7 percent to 4,521.01. The  MSCI
Chile index  fell 0.3 percent to 2,580.99.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU)   dropped 3.5 percent to
6,728.7 pesos in a fifth day of declines, its longest losing
streak since August. Chile’s biggest brewer fell to a two-month
low after first-quarter profit trailed analysts’ estimates on
higher marketing costs and Bank of America Merrill Lynch cut the
company to neutral from buy.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD)   fell 1 percent to 2,982.5 pesos
in its second day of losses. Regulators ordered the country’s
largest retailer by sales to close one of its supermarkets after
a sanitation violation, Diario Financiero reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
